<h2>{% trans %}Design summary{% endtrans %}</h2>
<p>{% trans %}The bm_help_ai_design_document.md file describes the intent to aggregate Drupal help systems, maintain canonical authorship, and introduce AI strictly as an enhancement for relevance and synthesis.{% endtrans %}</p>

<h3>{% trans %}Guiding principles{% endtrans %}</h3>
<ul>
  <li>{% trans %}Authoritative help remains static; AI cannot rewrite documentation.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Aggregation over replacement; existing help APIs stay intact.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Explicit metadata drives placement; no implicit ownership guessing.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Graceful degradation keeps the page functional without AI.{% endtrans %}</li>
</ul>

<h3>{% trans %}Future AI scope{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>{% trans %}Planned AI work is limited to ranking, grouping, and summarization of existing help. Any AI output must be traceable back to authoritative sources.{% endtrans %}</p>

<p>{% trans %}Refer to the repository copy of bm_help_ai_design_document.md for full background, architecture, and non-goals.{% endtrans %}</p>
